The paper deals with the problem of identifying credible reviews, which is a common issue in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The approach presented in the paper involves the use of latent topic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the development of models for computing review credibility scores, which involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of transferability of the models to other domains, which is a common concern in the field of cybersecurity (cs.CY).
